50|$|Forward {{induction}} is {{so called}} because just as backward induction assumes future play will be rational, forward induction assumes past play was rational. Where a player {{does not know}} what type another player is (i.e. there is imperfect and asymmetric information), <b>that</b> <b>player</b> may form a belief of what type <b>that</b> <b>player</b> is by observing <b>that</b> <b>player's</b> past actions. Hence the belief formed by <b>that</b> <b>player</b> of what the probability of the opponent being a certain type is based on the past play of that opponent being rational. A player may elect to signal his type through his actions.|$|R
