5|$|Before the game's release, {{industry}} analyst Michael Pachter estimated that Halo Wars would sell 2 million units. On March 19, 2009, Microsoft {{announced that the}} game had sold 1 million units and <b>that</b> <b>players</b> had spent 118 total years of time in online skirmish matches. According to NPD Group's March sales figures, Halo Wars sold 639,000 copies in the U.S. through March, making it the third best-selling game in the market.|$|E
